      <h2>Marketing priorities for digital product shops</h2>
      <p>Digital product shops break when email treats every subscriber the same. The pressure point is delivery, onboarding, cross-sells, and low-inventory constraints. A disciplined email marketing program must coordinate consent, lifecycle timing, product context, and margin-aware measurement — not blast more coupons.</p>
      <p>Priority plays: Instant delivery and access emails; Onboarding and activation series; Cross-sell by purchase behavior; Renewal and upgrade paths. Document suppressions for recent purchasers, wholesale accounts, and active support cases before scaling sends.</p>
      <p>Sequenzy ranks first for digital product shops because lifecycle editorial beats newsletter volume: welcome by signup source, replenishment matched to consumption, winback with VIP exclusions.</p>
      <p>Klaviyo remains the benchmark when digital product shops need predictive segmentation and native Shopify event depth at scale. Omnisend wins when email + SMS must go live before month end.</p>
      <p>Track Activation rate post-purchase, Cross-sell within 14 days, Renewal conversion, Support ticket reduction from onboarding weekly. Email ROI appears when incremental repeat purchase rises while unsubscribe and complaint rates stay flat.</p>
      <p>Buying cycle reality: Immediate delivery; onboarding critical; cross-sell within 7 days. Email cadence must respect that rhythm — not the marketing calendar alone.</p>
      <p>Implementation: audit consent sources in week one, launch welcome segmented by source in week two, add cart or post-purchase in week three, measure repeat purchase movement in week four.</p>
      <p>Peak season for digital product shops requires pausing non-essential flows, protecting VIP segments, and aligning merchandising with inbox promises — governance matters more than new app installs.</p>
      <p>Deliverability note: digital product shops with aggressive promos need authentication, frequency caps, and sunset policies — complaint spikes often trace to offer mismatch, not weak templates.</p>
      <p>Pair capture tools (Privy, Justuno) only when list growth is the leak; pair Postscript when SMS recovery justifies cost. Avoid three senders without a collision calendar.</p>
      <p>Read comparisons and use-case playbooks on this site for head-to-head tradeoffs and execution detail specific to delivery, onboarding, cross-sells, and low-inventory constraints.</p>
      <h3>Where digital product operators leak revenue</h3>
      <p>Cross-sell before activation. Review asks before first login. Bundle purchasers in one generic welcome. Renewal and upgrade promos colliding with onboarding. Affiliate offers interrupting day-one access.</p>
      <p>Reading path for digital: minute-zero delivery in Sequenzy; {segment.metrics[0]} gate before {segment.metrics[1]}; {segment.emailPriorities.join('; ')}. {segment.buyingCycle} — Shopify email marketing apps optimize activation speed, not promo volume.</p>
